annotation.TEXT: And it doesn't look like I've missed anything else. (At least I hope not...)
Man, the way this hack has hidden some of its secrets is getting me into the habit of checking a lot of plain ol' walls now!
Well, that's kind of a bummer, but I guess I'm nearing the end of this demo, so 2-4 and I assume 2-5 afterwards may be the last remaining playable levels. Okay, so let's start 2-4!
Ooh, multi-coin block underwater. How well can I score?
To be continued...
Okay, so where will I be heading next? Into the pipe in the upper-left? Or into Level 2-4 in the upper-right?
Huh. That second Urchin made kind of an odd movement there...
I can spin jump off these Blarggs safely, right? Yeah, there's no problem with that, as long as I aim right.
I'll get rid of this Swooper first to make sure he won't get in my way. Now, let's do this thing!
GAAAMMMEEE!!! Quit doing that! What's with these coins anyway?
Bonk! And the second fish didn't even need to be fried. Okay, so there's midpoint, another light switch, and a pipe that I assume is where I'd come from if I entered the level from midpoint.
Alright, so like I said, I'm going to just take a peek at that pipe first...
Gotta check almost every wall, ceiling, and floor...
28 coins. I feel like I could've done better than that...
Okay, now I can go back and get that coin, by refrying that fish!
And there's more of those gray ! blocks that I've grown to hate (except for certain ones in 2-3 that were actually helpful).
And inside we have a MOOOOOOONNNNNN!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! (Got enough exclamation points there?)
Well, I've tallied up the votes (hopefully accurately), and typed them into Notepad once again, so let me just bring that program up once again...
Ha! I managed to get that fishy coin that time!
Aw, nuts. Well, so much for potentially exploring any secret levels beyond 2-4... Also, I think there should be the word "in" after "anywhere".
I did see those blue coins up there. I'll look for a way to reach them after I'm done collecting these yellow coins.
Now, if you ride the raft down here, you can jump to where the P-switch is without needing to go through that side area first.
I didn't miss anything up here, did I? Nope. Uh, oh. Looks like the Urchins are trying to gang up on me, but I should just be able to duck under them all...
Wait, what? Did I just wall jump twice in a row off the same wall?
Alright, let's hope I have enough time to reach an exit (either one).
However, as it turns out, it ultimately didn't matter how you guys voted this time, because this pipe doesn't work. I'm mashing A, B, X, and Y repeatedly on it, and nothing's happening.
It must have been specially programmed to avoid crashing the universe. Oh, well...
Moon count: 4
Double kill!
Alright, so now that I've found a light switch, I'm going to fully explore everywhere back here, and risk running out of time.
BGM: Blocks That Matter - Star
Hello, and welcome back to... whatever the name of this hack is. Now, before I bring up the voting results, once again, I gotta revisit a level to show something off...
Whoop! Once again, I'm almost getting too hasty to grab a power up right there that I can use.
Doesn't look like there's anything else here, so let's just exit the level off the left side of the screen here.
(And of course, I continue to waste time searching every corner...)
Argh! Why do I keep occasionally passing through coins?
Also, sorry, but I don't think I'll be committing suicide any number of times on purpose here, but who knows? Maybe a level will be nasty enough to take away 9 of my lives!
Don't worry. I'm not going to forget about that Yoshi coin down there.
And, as it turns out, you can indeed toss the P-switch to the level above. I just sucked at doing that before.
Ooh, there's something over here... Meh, it's just 21 coins.

Huzzah! Yes, there is indeed a secret P-switch door over here that I would never had known about if Shott133 (who is actually TRS, the maker of this hack) hadn't informed me about it with that "Just a thing" video!
Okay, can I do better at this multi-coin block this time?
Uh, oh. No light switch this time. I guess I'd better follow the money while constantly firing fireballs.
Bah! I knew it was a bad idea to try going for that Yoshi coin from that angle...
Double kill!
Sorry, but I couldn't seem to find a picture of Mario eating a ham...

Alright, and that unlocks 2-5. Hmm... Should I try to squeeze it into this video? Umm... Actually, I'm already over 11 minutes here, and I don't want to make another 20-minute+ marathon episode right now, so this level will have to wait until next time!
Nuts. I thought for a split-second that there might be a secret up there...
Yes! I didn't quite put enough oomph into my first jump there, which threw off my rhythm (which is why I stopped jumping for a couple seconds), but I recovered and still got the perfect!
Whoops! I guess I'm not getting that coin, at least right now.
Okay, I'm not going to be an idiot when it comes to this Yoshi coin this time.
Ooh, 31 coins! That's really good! I wonder if it's reasonably possible to get the normal maximum of 32 coins that way?
Aww... Why can't I divide by zero?!
Okay, so that's how I reach these dozen blue coins, but that appears to be all there is up here...
It's pitch black. You are likely to be eaten by a grue.
GAAAMMMEEE!!! That stupid slanted ceiling screwed up my fireball!
Uh, oh... Well, that was dumb of me...
Why is this important? Well, you'll see in a moment. Now, let's see if I can do this on my first try...
(Insert overused Flame Hyenard lines here.)
Oh, I can so totally fry that first fish! (Too bad its coin is now eternally stuck...)
Yep, so as that message mentioned, no additional paths opened up. Well, let's go back and get the normal exit now.
Man, did you see that? Them Urchins tried to troll me, man!
Ooh, there's something potentially important this way...
I see that up there! (It's kind of hard to miss, actually.)
Oh, I probably caught on the side of the pipe in that instance, allowing me to wall jump a second time in a row off of it.
Okay, no more need to worry about grues now. Also, apparently this whole place is underwater. Kind of reminds me of Glimmer's Galleon in DKC2, actually.
Oh, come on! GAAAMMMEEE!!! At least I can still escape up here.
Well, this level's done, and I'm probably going to be playing the bonus game for the last time in this hack right here. Let's make it a good one!
So, we start off by fishing for green coins, and frying fish.
Oh, good. There's the secret exit right there, so I don't have to worry about timing out this time.
Oh, yeah. That's the red pipe that led to the secret exit.
